post.description:
Refund a guest escrow payment.

Since guests have no internal wallet, this triggers a refund via the
original payment provider (Stripe or Monime) and debits the escrow wallet.

The flow runs in three phases so the provider HTTP call never happens
while we hold DB row locks:
  A) lock the transaction row, validate, mark it refund_pending, commit;
  B) call the provider (idempotency-keyed, no locks held);
  C) lock again, debit escrow, mark refunded, commit.
A transaction stuck in refund_pending (crash mid-flow) can be retried:
phase A accepts it and the provider idempotency key makes B safe.
